author.value: Collection processed by Archives staff.  Finding aid created by Julianna Monjeau.

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2018-06-14T21:05:06</date>

unittitle.value: Records of the Office of the Associate Dean of Libraries

extent.value: in 6 record cartons and 3 manuscript boxes

abstract.value: This collection contains material associated with the administration of the Associate Dean, including memoranda, reports, meeting minutes, correspondence and other documentation. An additional accession of material includes VHS tapes and audio cassettes of library meetings and events and library publications in addition to the assorted administrative materials. This collection was donated by Associate Dean Nancy Kranich but contains the records and correspondence of her predecessors and the Dean of libraries.

p.value: Materials are restricted for twenty years from the date of creation. This collection is in off-site storage.

Published citations should take the following form: Identification of item, date (if known); Records of the Office of the Associate Dean of Libraries; RG 38.0.1; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.

The earliest Associate Dean is Eugene P. Kennedy, who served from 1971-1973, and whose responsibilities included managing the newly constructed Bobst Library. Nancy Kranich served as Associate Dean from 1992-2001 before assuming the presidency of the American Library Association.

Accession 03-004 initially contained correspondence, memoranda, reports, publications, VHS tapes and audio cassettes from the Associate Dean's office. The reports and publications from this accession were transferred to the New-York Historical Society and the audio-visual material was separated from the collection and transferred to the Audio Visual Collection for preservation.
